quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  34,46,"Say, “ I admonish you only for one thing, that you stand in pairs and singly for the sake of Allah then reflect, your companion is not under the influence of a jinn, he is only a warner (sent) to you before a severe punishment.”"
  34,47,"Say, “I do not ask you for a reward, but ( that which I ask you to do) is for your (benefit, the responsibility of) rewarding me (rests on none) but Allah and He is a Witness over everything.”"
  34,48,"Say, “My Fosterer certainly strikes through the truth, Great Knower of the unseen.”"
  34,49,"Say, “The truth has come and nothing is originated or reproduced by falsehood.”"
  34,50,"Say, “ If I err, I err only against my own soul and if I am guided then it is because of that which my Fosterer has communicated to me, He is certainly Hearing, Near.”"
  34,51,"And if you could only see when they are horrified, then there will be no escape, and they will be caught from a near place"
  34,52,"And they will say, “We believe in it.” But how can they seek (to believe) from such a distant place"
  34,53,"when they did not believe init earlier? And they strike (guesses) regarding the unseen, from a distance place"
  34,54,"And a barrier will be placed between them and that which they desire, as was done with the parties (like) them earlier, they certainly used to be in doubt causing restlessness"